  "@type": "Capability",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Raising domesticated rabbits (Oryctolagus cuniculus) for meat, fur, and Angora wool. Rabbits produce 4-6 litters of 6-12 kits per year, reaching processing weight (2-2.5 kg) at 10-12 weeks on minimal space (0.15-0.25 m² per kg). Rabbit manure can be applied directly to crops without composting (cold manure).",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Fastest reproduction of any livestock — a single doe can produce 100+ kg of meat per year. Minimal space, feed, and infrastructure requirements.",
